<nav class="nav" id="nav" data-screen-label="Nav"><svg class="sunmark" viewBox="0 0 32 32" aria-hidden="true"><circle class="sun-disc" cx="16" cy="16" r="10"></circle></svg><a class="wm" href="/">AMPM <small>BUILDING SERVICES</small></a><div class="links"><a href="/services/" class="">Services</a><a href="/work/" class="">Work</a><a href="/compliance/" class="">Compliance</a><a href="/about/" class="">About</a><a href="/contact/" class="">Contact</a></div><a class="phone" href="tel:03300430080">0330 043 0080</a></nav><div class="page" style="--svc: var(--m-purple);"><div class="shell"><section class="sec p-hero"><div class="reveal in"><span class="svc-bar" style="background: var(--m-purple);"></span></div><div class="reveal in"><div class="kicker">Commercial Fit-out</div></div><h1 class="reveal d1 in">Integrated M&amp;E</h1><p class="lede reveal d2 in">Integrated mechanical &amp; electrical within the fit-out across London and the South East — the M&amp;E held in-house rather than sub-let. One contractor for the services and the fabric, with fire-stopping, compartmentation and commissioning built into the same programme, not split across two trades.</p><div class="reveal d3 in" style="margin-top: 28px;"><a class="btn line sm" href="/contact/">Enquire about Integrated M&amp;E →</a></div></section><section class="sec tight"><div class="reveal in" style="margin-bottom: 32px;"><div class="kicker">What we deliver</div><h2 class="dhead sm">Integrated M&amp;E,<br>self-delivered.</h2></div><div class="capgroups reveal in"><div class="capgroup"><h4><span class="dot" style="background: var(--m-purple);"></span><span>Scope</span></h4><ul><li>Coordinated mechanical &amp; electrical within the fit-out</li><li>One contractor, one programme — no services / fabric split</li><li>Fire-stopping &amp; compartmentation, installed and recorded</li><li>Commissioning, demonstration &amp; witnessing</li><li>Full O&amp;M manuals &amp; as-built records at handover</li><li>A single snag list across services and fabric</li></ul></div><div class="capgroup"><h4><span class="dot" style="background: var(--m-purple);"></span><span>Standards &amp; compliance</span></h4><ul><li>BS 7671 — IET Wiring Regulations</li><li>CIBSE &amp; BSRIA commissioning codes</li><li>Building Regulations Part B — fire safety</li><li>CDM 2015 across every package</li></ul></div></div></section><section class="sec tight"><div class="reveal in" style="margin-bottom: 28px;"><div class="kicker">FAQs</div><h2 class="dhead sm">Your questions,<br>answered.</h2></div><div class="faq reveal in"><details class="faq-item"><summary>Why keep the M&amp;E in-house rather than sub-let it?</summary><p>Sub-letting the M&amp;E is the most common source of programme slip on a fit-out — the services and the fabric fall between two trades. We hold the M&amp;E in-house, so one contractor and one project manager carry the whole floor, services included.</p></details><details class="faq-item"><summary>Do you cover fire-stopping and compartmentation?</summary><p>Yes. Fire-stopping and compartmentation are built into the package — installed and recorded to support compliance with Building Regulations Part B. Because the M&amp;E and the fabric are the same contractor, every penetration is sealed and logged, not left between trades.</p></details><details class="faq-item"><summary>What do we get at commissioning and handover?</summary><p>A managed commissioning, demonstration and witnessing process to the CIBSE and BSRIA codes, then a clean handover with full O&amp;M manuals and as-built records. With one contractor, it's a single snag list across services and fabric, not two.</p></details><details class="faq-item"><summary>Which areas do you cover?</summary><p>London and the South East, including Sussex, Surrey, Kent, Hampshire and Berkshire.</p></details></div></section><section class="sec tight"><div class="reveal in" style="margin-bottom: 28px;"><div class="kicker">Part of Commercial Fit-out</div><h2 class="d